4. Bh4 {[%mdl 32768]} ( { In this particular position, } 4.Bxf6 { is also a fine alternative followed by e4 and c3. However, Black remains solid and has an advantage long term due to the bishop pair. Because of this, I suggest sticking with our usual response. } ) g5 { Black has always had this option and, to be fair, it's a very fine alternative! Our bishop will probably be exchanged by Black's knight, and Black has the additional possibility to develop their bishop via g7. In exchange, Black will remain overextended and some squares around the kingside will be potentially weak. As such, it will be harder for Black to castle on this side of the board. } 
5. Bg3 Ne4 
6. Nbd2 { Black will get the bishop pair, but we'll have a good grip in the center. Also, Black has now permanent weaknesses on the kingside. } Nxg3 
