9. Bf4 {[%cal Gd1c2,Gf3g5]} { This is the simplest move. We don't want to exchange pieces when we are attacking, so we retreat our bishop to f4. Also, the g5-square can be occupied by our knight, which would pose more threats; Qc2 or Ng5 are usually next. } Bd6 { Black continues harassing our bishop! } 
10. Ng5 { Not the only move, but the most direct one! } Bxf4 { This is almost forced to get a playable position. } 
