12. Qc2 {[%mdl 32768]} { As usual, we put pressure on Black with every move. } Nd7 { Only move, Black needs to develop. } ( 12...Nxg5? 13.hxg5 g6 14.Nf3 $18 { , other moves were also good enough. Our plan is simple: we are going to castle long (or even play Ke2 in some cases), double on the h-file, and mate Black! White is winning. } ) 
13. Ndxe4 ( { Good enough. We win a pawn and end up in a very comfortable position. } 13.f3 { is also possible if you prefer to go for the attack. } ) dxe4 
14. Bxe4 Bxe4 
15. Qxe4 Nf6 
16. Qe5 { All of Black's moves until here were forced. The position has simplified, but we remain a pawn up with very good winning chances. We plan to castle at some point, with both short and long castling possible, aiming to maintain the initiative. } cxd4 
