1. d4 f5 { This is the beginning of the so-called Dutch Defense, which is very popular at the club level! } 
2. Nf3 { Our usual 2nd move, also effective against the Dutch Defense. In many cases, our idea will be to try to play for an early e4 break, sometimes supported by our beloved bishop on g5! Now, Black has several options. } d6 { A flexible move that prepares, among others, the Dutch Leningrad where Black plays with ...Nf6, ...g6, and ...Bg7. } 
3. c3 { Only the 6th most popular move, with only 1% of the games reaching this position. Our plan is to play Bg5 and Nbd2, similarly to other main Torre lines! However, since we cannot play Bg5 under good conditions because of ...h6, we play this waiting move. } ( 3.c3 { Now, Black has two main options to continue with the Leningrad development: } 3...Nf6 { or } ( 3...g6 { . } ) ) e6 ( 3...e6 { This move has never been played at the master level, but it's interesting against our setup, as now } 4.Bg5 { wouldn't be so strong because of } 4...Be7 { . } ) 
4. h4 $146  ( { We've seen this move against ...g6 setups. In this case, it's more of a waiting move to see how Black develops. The move is a bit speculative but by no means wrong! In any case, I also offer } 4.Qc2 { as a more 'sensible' alternative [/variation/43295036/#/4/w]. } ) Nf6 
5. Bg5 {[%cal Gb1d2,Ge2e4]} { Of course, this was our idea, as now we can play our desired Bg5. The idea is similar to other lines now: Nbd2 and e4. } Be7 
6. Nbd2 Nbd7 { This is an accurate move order for Black, as it temporarily stops e4. } 
7. Qc2 {[%mdl 32768]} {[%cal Ge2e4]} { Supporting e4 again! } h6 
8. Bxf6 Nxf6 
9. e4 { Finally, e4 is on the board! :) } O-O 
10. Bd3 { We've developed harmonically, and Black is under a bit of pressure. } Ng4 { This is the most accurate move for Black, defending f5 and taking advantage of our pawn on h4  -  it cannot go backwards, unfortunately! } 
11. Nf1 $36  {[%cal Gf1g3,Ge1c1]} { This is a very interesting maneuver to remember! We are planning to play Ng3 next and also defend the f2-pawn with our queen, so O-O-O is now possible! The position is double-edged, with chances for both sides. } *

