1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} { In various World Rapid and Blitz championships, Magnus has employed the London System and the Torre Attack as main weapons! } Nf6 
2. Nf3 g6 
3. Bg5 Bg7 
4. Nbd2 d6 
5. c3 h6 
6. Bh4 g5 
7. Bg3 Nh5 { Black goes after the bishop pair but weakens the kingside quite a bit! } 
8. e4 Nxg3 
9. hxg3 { It is usually best to bring pawns towards the center! } c5 
10. dxc5 ( 10.d5 { is the move that the engine prefers! When Black develops the knight to d7, playing g4 can be interesting in certain positions, stopping ...f5 for good! } ) dxc5 
11. Bc4 {[%csl Rf7]} { The best square for the bishop, targeting f7. } Qb6 
12. Rb1 ( 12.Qc2 { is preferable, and this position even allows White to go long castle in some cases. } ) Be6 $6  { I'm unsure if trading the light-squared bishops is Black's best idea since Black would lose the bishop pair, but I understand that the bishop on c4 is scary! } 
13. O-O Nd7 
14. Bd5 $5  { Very smart move from Magnus. Now, if Black opts to trade, he will retain a backward pawn on e7 that can be easily targeted. Magnus also frees the c4-square for his knight! } Bg4 $6  
15. Nc4 Qc7 
16. Qb3 {[%csl Rb7,Rf7]} { Now, Black is in deep trouble since White is putting pressure on b7 and indirect pressure on f7! } O-O-O ( 16...Rb8? { The natural defense does not work because of } 17.Bxf7+ Kxf7 18.Nce5+ { with Qf7+ coming, winning the game. } ) 
17. Na5! { The knight is untouchable because of Qxb7#. } b6 
18. Nc6 e6 ( 18...Rde8 { runs into } 19.Qa4 19...a5 20.b4 { and the attack is too strong! } ) 
19. Nxd8 Rxd8 
20. Bc4 { The rest of the game is an easy job for Magnus! } Bxf3 
21. gxf3 Ne5 
22. Kg2 h5 
23. Rbd1 Rh8 
24. Be2 h4 
25. Rh1 Kb8 
26. Qc2 Qc6 
27. Qd2 g4 
28. Rxh4 1-0

